Looking at the proof goal, I need to show that for any point `x : X` in a diffeological manifold, there exists an open neighborhood diffeomorphic to an open subset of the half-space `{x : Eucl n | 0 ≤ x 0}`.

I already have:
- `u : Set X` - an open set containing `x`
- `v : Set (Eucl n)` - an open set in `Eucl n`
- `d : ↑u ᵈ≃ ↑v` - a diffeomorphism between them

Since `Eucl n` naturally embeds into the half-space `{x : Eucl n | 0 ≤ x 0}` (any open set in `Eucl n` can be viewed as an open set in the half-space with the subspace topology), I can use `v` directly as an open subset of the half-space.

```lean
/-- Any diffeological manifold is also a diffeological manifold with boundary. -/
instance {n : ℕ} {X : Type*} [Zero (Fin n)] [DiffeologicalSpace X]
    [hm : IsDiffeologicalManifold n X] : IsManifoldWithBoundary n X := ⟨fun x ↦ by
  let ⟨u,hu,hxu,i,v,hv,⟨d⟩⟩ := hm.locally_modelled x
  refine ⟨u,hu,hxu,(),Subtype.val ⁻¹' v,hv.preimage continuous_subtype_val,⟨?_⟩⟩
  exact d.trans (DDiffeomorph.Set.nested v)⟩
```
